<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="constant-adj">constant <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'kɒnstənt/    美 /'kɑːnstənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>固定的；不变的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a constant temperature
恒温</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>drive at a constant speed
匀速驾驶</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>不停的；连续不断的；持续的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a constant stream of visitors 
络绎不绝的游客</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A constant dropping wears the stone.
滴水穿石。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She needed constant medical attention.
她需要不间断的医疗护理。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>constantly /'kɒnstəntli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The Forbidden City attracts <strong><em>_</em></strong>_  (络绎不绝的游客) every day, especially during national holidays.  （2013 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. a constant stream of visitors / tourists  </p></div>